<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-08-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="119" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Jernigan</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Denby.</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-08-25"><hi rend="smallcaps">August</hi> 25,
                                    1894</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Arrested on concession, peacefully and openly engaged away from seat of
                            war; not a Japanese soldier on Chinese soil at the time. Mere
                            schoolboys. China can well afford to have us keep them secure.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Jernigan.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>